title: Frieze, 1905–15
inscribed: Printed in selvedge: "S. A. Maxwell & Co." "2156"
description:
Repeating yellow rose wreaths (each with six flowers) over/attached to drapery swags tied in bows that connect to a thin horizontal twisting ribbon. Above the swags is lattice pattern in dark red and two thin green stripes. Below the wreathers is a scroll pattern with floral bands. At the bottom are two green stripes. Grounding is shaded from dark red to light pink (bottom to top). Printed in gold mica, greens, pinks, yellows, and reds.
Printed in selvedge: "S. A. Maxwell & Co." "2156"

Frieze, 1905–15.
